        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "v.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 8) her master’s concubine; she stood consequently to her master in a relation which could not suitably be terminated at the end of six years. Concubinage was common among the ancient Hebrews (among the patriarchs, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
